\"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\"}, {\"begin\": 735, \"end\": 740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rosey_(wrestler)\", \"score\": 0.9989171603741043, \"rank\": 0.0005420054200540739, \"text\": \"Rosey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rosey_(wrestler)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rosey_(wrestler)\"}, {\"begin\": 754, \"end\": 759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999405454236, \"rank\": 5.9454489552418223e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Racing in heat 2 of 5, Bailey posted a time of 44.86 as runner-up and was third best overall.\", \"from\": 797, \"to\": 890, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 820, \"end\": 826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Homer_Bailey\", \"score\": 0.9741219036699544, \"rank\": 0.023704217150396056, \"text\": \"Bailey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Homer_Bailey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Homer_Bailey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The fifth heat featured two Razorbacks in adjacent lanes as Tomlyanovich finished third in 45.76 while Benson placed fourth in 45.81.\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 1024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 994, \"end\": 1000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kris_Benson\", \"score\": 0.9981884990016352, \"rank\": 0.0018147884894198275, \"text\": \"Benson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kris_Benson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kris_Benson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's semifinal will be held on Sunday.\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1068, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Following Little's leading time were Georgia's Aaliyah Butler (50.44) and Lynna Irby-Jackson (50.89).\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1107, \"end\": 1114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\", \"score\": 0.9744261938539367, \"rank\": 0.024535336687653328, \"text\": \"Georgia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\"}, {\"begin\": 1117, \"end\": 1124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aaliyah\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.118514321050098e-19, \"text\": \"Aaliyah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aaliyah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aaliyah\"}, {\"begin\": 1125, \"end\": 1131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Butler_Bulldogs_men's_basketball\", \"score\": 0.9999999594829213, \"rank\": 2.8248185866831295e-08, \"text\": \"Butler\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Butler_Bulldogs_men's_basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Butler_Bulldogs_men's_basketball\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Holmes won her heat in 51.05 ahead of a 51.21 for Effiong.\", \"from\": 1172, \"to\": 1230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1172, \"end\": 1178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"score\": 0.9839917919825635, \"rank\": 0.01626711379599035, \"text\": \"Holmes\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brown placed third in another heat with a 51.09 while Peoples clocked 52.20 for fourth in the same heat with Little.\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1347, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The women's semifinal is on Saturday.\", \"from\": 1348, \"to\": 1385, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Crouser hit a mark of 70-4.25 (21.44) in his outdoor debut that was third best in the qualifying round.\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1490, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"An opening round mark of 65-4.75 (19.93) by Jordan West placed 10th overall and advanced to Saturday's final.\", \"from\": 1491, \"to\": 1600, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1535, \"end\": 1541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Grand_Prix\", \"score\": 0.6810290992629771, \"rank\": 0.4651155488861414, \"text\": \"Jordan\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Grand_Prix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Grand_Prix\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gregory finished ninth in the first heat of the 5,000m in 15:25.80 and earned a time qualifier to Monday evening's 10-person final.\", \"from\": 1602, \"to\": 1733, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Elle St. Pierre led the field with a 15:13.82 over a 15:15.42 from Karissa Schweizer from the same heat.\", \"from\": 1734, \"to\": 1838, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1734, \"end\": 1738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elle_King\", \"score\": 0.9239736334305687, \"rank\": 0.0812689925915351, \"text\": \"Elle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elle_King\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elle_King\"}, {\"begin\": 1801, \"end\": 1818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karissa_Schweizer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karissa Schweizer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karissa_Schweizer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karissa_Schweizer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jada Baylark posted a wind-assisted 11.12 (3.1w) to finish fifth in her 100m heat and auto qualified for the semifinal.\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 1959, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1840, \"end\": 1844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jada_Pinkett_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5412660068539606e-20, \"text\": \"Jada\"